      "title": "Overview",
      "description": "## Overview\n\nTrue MFA means that you authenticate with at least two factors of different types. A password is a knowledge factor. There are also possession and inherence factors. For this lab, we'll configure a possession factor using the Auth0 Guardian app.\n\n**Here's an overview of what you'll do:**  \n\n1.  Enable Push factor via Auth0 Guardian\n1.  Enforce MFA for all users in your tenant\n1.  Reset MFA for a user"
    },
    {
      "file": "README.md",
      "line": 1,
      "title": "Enable the Push factor via Auth0 Guardian",
      "description": "## Enable Push factor via Auth0 Guardian\n\n_This optional exercise requires you to install the Auth0 Guardian app on a supported device. If you are unable to install apps on an iOS or Android device, you can skip this exercise._\n\nAuth0 Guardian is a mobile app that can deliver push notifications to a user’s pre-registered device - typically a mobile phone or tablet - from which a user can immediately allow or deny account access via the press of a button. It can also generate one-time passwords if that factor is preferred.  \n\n1. #### Install the Auth0 Guardian App if you do not already have it:\n    *   [iOS](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/auth0-guardian/id1093447833)\n    *   [Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.auth0.guardian)\n\n1. #### Enable Auth0 Guardian Push Notifications\n    1. Navigate to _Security > Multi-factor Auth_.  \n    1. Click on _Push Notifications using Auth0 Guardian_. \n    1. Click the toggle button on Auth0 Guardian page to enable this factor. \n    1. Click the _Back to Multi-factor Authentication_ link.\n    1. You should now see that _Push Notifications using Auth0 Guardian_ is _Enabled_\n\n\nNote that a warning banner appears. For training purposes, we can enable Push Notifications using Auth0 Guardian. However, to use this feature in production you will need an active Enterprise subscription. "
    },
    {
      "title": "Try It Out",
      "description": "## Try It Out - Uh Oh!\n\n1. #### Click [here](command:workbench.action.debug.start) to deploy the _Lab: Web App_.\n    \n    Give the app a few moments to deploy. (You can watch the debug terminal to see when it's finished.)\n    \n1. #### Ensure the ports are public so that the SPA app and API can communicate. Click the ports tab below, then right click each endpoint, and change the port visibility to public. \n    \n    ![](https://cdn.auth0.com/website/auth0/labs/ilt/public-ports.gif)\n\n\n\n3. #### Click [here](command:auth0.lab.openEndpointByName?[\"Lab: Web App, Lab: API\"]) to open the app in your browser and test logging in.\n    \n    You may need to log out fully before attempting to log in. \n    To do so, navigate to: https://{yourTenantName}.{yourRegion}.auth0.com/v2/logout\n    \n\n2. #### You’ll note that you’re not challenged for a second factor. Although you have enabled the _Push Notifications using Auth0 Guardian_ factor for the account, you have not yet set up your tenant to require its use.\n\n![try it out](https://cdn.auth0.com/website/a0fun/v2/mfa-6.gif)\n\nLet's fix this by enforcing MFA for all users."
    },
