    {
      "title": "Test MFA Enrollment",
      "description": "## Test MFA Enrollment\n\n1. #### Return to the _Lab: Web App_ in your browser and test logging in again, with the same credentials. (You'll need to log out first.)\n      \n    After entering the credentials for the MFA protected user, you are now prompted to set up _Auth0 Guardian_.  \n    \n1. #### Click the _Continue_ button.\n    \n1. #### You’ll see a QR code displayed. Open the Guardian app on your device, and tap the _+_ in the top right corner. \n    Note, if this is the first time you’ve used Guardian on your device, you will be prompted to allow the app to use your camera in order to scan the QR code.  You do NOT need to allow the app to collect usage data.\n    \n1. #### Now scan the QR code. You may need to allow the app to send push notifications.\n    The Guardian app will create a new entry with your tenant name and your email address.    \n    \n    \n   \n1. #### In your browser window note the _Authorize App_ dialog is displayed. Press _Accept_. You’ll be logged into the app. \n    \n    \n1. #### Go to the Details view of the MFA user in _Dashboard > User Management > Users_. \n    Note that your device is now listed as an MFA factor with the message _Enrolled using Push Notification and TOTP_.  \n ",
